text: The room was clean, neat and comfortable.  I stayed 2 nights, slept well both nights. Wear a sleep mask because there is a street light out front.  I was grateful to find these accommodations so close to the convention center.  Three days parking downtown was almost the price of the room before tax. title: Loved my stay here
text: OK, seriously the owner, Maclir goes above and beyond. You can tell he really wants his guests to have a good experience and is passionate about his place. First off, he reached out to me before I arrived and offered to come pick me up from the ferry for a small fee. I have NEVER had anyone from a hostel do this. This was way better than getting a taxi and he popped out of no where at the pier it was so welcoming and honestly set the tone for how amazing my experience was in this island. As soon as we arrived to the home stay he gave me a run down about the island. Which beaches to go, where to eat and what there is to do. Again, goes above and beyond. I ended up having to move to a new location since he was fully booked and I wanted to stay longer which I was a little sad about but he even helped me move my stuff to my new place. Like I said he‚Äôs a really good guy and willing to always help out his guests. The rooms were cute, he definitely keeps up with them and even makes your bed for you which I appreciated. I was amazing at how on point he is!
